from flask import Flask, request, jsonify from flask_cors import CORS import joblib import numpy as np app = Flask(_name_) CORS(app)  # Enable CORS # Load the trained Crop Recommendation model crop_model = joblib.load("C:/Users/LENOVO/OneDrive/Desktop/project/model/crop_recommendation.pkl")  # Update with your model path @app.route("/crop-recommend", methods=["POST"]) def crop_recommend():     try:         data = request.json  # Get JSON data from request         features = [             float(data["nitrogen"]),             float(data["phosphorous"]),             float(data["potassium"]),             float(data["phLevel"]),             float(data["rainfall"]),         ]         # Convert to numpy array and reshape         features = np.array(features).reshape(1, -1)         # Get model prediction         prediction = crop_model.predict(features)[0]         return jsonify({"recommended_crop": prediction})     except Exception as e:         return jsonify({"error": str(e)}), 500 if _name_ == "_main_":     app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=5001, debug=True)  # Running on a separate port
